The paper is about identifying self-admitted technical debt in software projects, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The approach proposed in the paper involves examining code comments, which could also fall under programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of technical debt on software maintenance, which could be relevant to software development (cs.SD) sub-category. The evaluation of the proposed approach involves using open-source projects, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the comparison of the proposed approach with state-of-the-art approaches, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
